The 17th byte overwrites only the LSB of the saved RBP — not the return address directly.
When do_copy() returns, main() restores the corrupted RBP. Its own 'ret' then reads an address from the wrong stack location.
Use gdb with 'stepi' and 'info registers' to watch rsp and rbp shift during the two nested returns.
The byte you inject should be the low byte of secret()'s address. Find it with: nm target | grep secret
